<TEXT>
christmas at the white house is a storybook 
affair this year with characters from childrens literature 
peeping out from the branches of an 18foot fraser fir decorated 
for the holidays 
barbara bush on monday gave reporters a tour of the lavish white 
house holiday decorations including the christmas tree in the blue 
room on the first floor 
with a theme that mrs bush said was a celebration of books 
and libraries the tree features 80 soft dolls representing 
characters from childrens books or literature 
among them are mary poppins babar the elephant the mad hatter 
tin man pinocchio scarlett ohara curious george the velveteen 
rabbit and aladdin 
mrs bush said she hoped her holiday choice will encourage 
families to read together 
there is sort of a little message to our christmas this year 
which is a family oriented reading to their children message 
she said 
tiny books also adorn the tree and beneath its branches are an 
array of books wrapped with bows 
the tree also features homemade decorated cookies and the 
traditional 100 4inch velvet balls two representing each state in 
the nation 
mrs bush said she began planning the christmas decorations in 
february with white house chief floral designer nancy clarke 
the entrance and cross halls feature 16 additional trees large 
blue spruces flocked with artificial snow and decorated with tiny 
white lights icicles and tinsel 
two more blue spruces stand at either end of the ceremonial east 
room ornately garlanded with copperred metallic ribbons and 
bursting with lifesize plastic grapes pears apples oranges 
tangerines and pomegranates 
also in the east room against a central mirror is displayed 
the baroque 48figure creche that has been in the white house each 
christmas since it was donated by a new jersey woman in 1967 
in the state dining room the central feature is a 36inch tall 
gingerbread house white house chef hans raffert has made a similar 
creation every year for 20 christmases 
the dining room also has two boxwood topiaries decorated with 
densely packed candy canes peppermint balls and cookies 
the entire bush clan five children spouses and 11 
grandchildren will accompany the president and mrs bush next 
week to the presidential retreat at camp david md for christmas 
mrs bush predicted chaos when the family opens gifts 
christmas morning 
she and the president will not exchange gifts 
we do not give presents the president and i she said 
adding that it is an arrangement they have followed for many years 
we felt we just had so much 
the white house decorations were put up over the weekend by 40 
volunteers 
we bounced up and down the stairs george and i talking to 
these people she said 
the bushes own christmas tree in their private upstairs 
quarters is decorated with cookies mrs bush said 
</TEXT>
