association of physics teachers and the national council of 
teachers of mathematics in a joint effort with the soviet unions 
academy of sciences 
but bill aldridge executive director of the nsta cautions that 
quantum is not for the average american student 
it is aimed at students who are curious and want to solve 
puzzles in physics and math aldridge said its aimed at the 
very able student 
most of the material in the first issue is based on articles and 
problems that first appeared in kvant a popular soviet magazine 
for high school students 
it includes problems in advanced geometry algebra and in basic 
physics all presented in a lively colorful way and applied to 
actual objects and observations 
