government has agreed to the establishment of corridors and said 
he had asked the rebel groups to do the same 
the primary corridor sought is a road extending sought from the 
red sea port of massawa which is controlled by the mengistu 
government into tigray a secondary corridor would be established 
from the red sea port of aseb southwestward through wello 
edelman said the announcement was being made because it has 
recently become apparent that the need is going to be much 
greater than we thought 
we do not believe it will be possible to avert starvation in 
northern ethiopia or to prevent large movements of people out of 
