to 40 million pounds initially is scheduled to begin operating in 
the spring of 1990 and will employ about 70 people 
noting that 60 percent of philadelphias neighborhoods already 
participate in recycling programs pappas said by locating the 
facility here we expect to be able to purchase a steady supply 
of source material and will have access to viable markets for the 
highvalue enduse products du pont intends to develop 
pappas said du pont expects to use the recycled plastics in the 
automotive consumer and building industries 
