to award punitive damages 
the jury found pratt amp whitney liable for the death of matthew 
macario 29 of coatesville pa who died feb 1 1985 when the 
beechcraft king air he was piloting crashed on approach to the 
millville nj airport copilot donald burns 58 of yardley 
pa also died 
the settlement requires the smallengine manufacturer to issue 
an urgent service bulletin advising aircraft owners that pratt 
amp whitney pt6 engines without a special filter could suddenly roll 
the engine back to idle and contribute to or cause a crash wolk 
said 
the bulletin will advise owners of the availability of p3 line 
filters that can reduce the possibility of fuel control unit 
contamination which causes the rollbacks he said 
a spokeswoman for pratt amp whitney louise boutin said the 
company had no immediate comment on the settlement she said the 
company has made the engine since 1963 but she had no estimate on 
the number produced 
the attorney for pratt amp whitney grant mccabe was ill tuesday 
and could not be reached for comment his assistant in the case 
lawrence wright refused to comment 
if this service bulletin saves just one life the time effort 
and cost of the trial will be worth it said wolk 
wolk claimed that pratt amp whitney knew about the potential 
problems in its engines without filters since 1973 he said some 
beechcraft aircraft but not all have the filter installed in 
their engines 
</TEXT>
